LAGOS – In its drive to leverage on cutting-edge technology to improve the quality of Mathematics and Science education in Nigeria, School Kits Limited has announce its partnership agreement with Casio Middle East to enhance the skills of 1,300 Maths and Science teachers. Temilola Adepetun, Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer School Kits, while speaking at the training, said that Casio’s Scientific Calculator has become an indispensable tool for every successful student across the world. She said that the training programme is a bold move to boost the knowledge of Mathematics and Science in Nigeria. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “As our world gets smaller and indeed more complex, Casio Middle East has innovatively iterated and designed scientific calculators capable of solving even more complex problems. It is indeed our hope that this training would add significant value to the development of Maths and Science education through capacity development and knowledge sharing for the teachers and by extension, students in Nigeria.